27/10/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Ion Iliescu kicked off an official three-day trip to the United States on Sunday (26 October), stopping first in Cleveland, Ohio, which is home to a large Romanian community.
In Washington, Iliescu is expected to meet US President George W. Bush, Secretary of State Colin Powell, Defence Secretary Donald Rumsfeld and Treasury Secretary John Snow.
Iliescu is also to talk with senior representatives of the World Bank and the IMF.
(ACT Media - 27/10/03;
Rompres, Mediafax, BBC - 26/10/03)
